<br>
As a result, I decided that dialup was still my best choice.  I used to play DAoC on anywhere from a 31k-48k connection and the only time I experience any horrific lag are during raid where there were upwards of 50+ people in one small area.  Otherwise I have no problems.  I don't have problems raiding in EQ either.  I've played EQ on the same connection for the past 2 years including numerous raids with very little trouble. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub49.ezboard.com/unyssarainwhisper.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nyssa Rainwhisper</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://arnemetia.homestead.com/files/MiscImages/roseicon.gif" BORDER=0> at: 5/30/02 12:36:52 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub49.ezboard.com/ucarydeconnla.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cary de Connla</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_greenspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Admin</span><br>  Posts: 172<br> <font color=#006400>(5/30/02 1:14:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub49.ezboard.com/fhiberniaonguiniverefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Satellite Connections</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the Insight!<br>
